Question: What type of cultural arts or entertainment opportunities would you like to see more of in Austin?

Response ID: resp_2380
Response Text: I don't want music in Austin to have to be just one thing. We have such a great jazz, indie-classical, classical scene...and so much more! I personally love what KMFA has built. I love their shows and their newsletter is my event guidepost. I have migraine and struggle with super loud venues so don't go to a lot of the traditional amplified Austin shows. I also love the opera and symphony and really appreciate when they do affordable tickets. 

I also would personally like to see more support go to organizations that provide access for everyday adult Austinites to PARTICIPATE in the arts and not just watch them. I often feel like local "audiences" are seen just as consumers and not possible participants too....we do better for kids but non-professional adults get really left out of the creation, which can be so healing!

